  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strengthening Community Driven Climate Resilience Building Initiatives in Mao-Komo  Woreda  of Benis</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall, long term change that this intervention seeks to contribute is enhanced resilience capacity of hard to reach and vulnerable communities to the current and future risks and hazards of climate change through promoting and generating evidences from community based climate change adaptation strategies, green energy technologies and practices. Successful demonstration of climate resilient technologies and practices in target area is also expected to result in initiated government and community adoption on climate smart technologies and livelihoods. Moreover, demonstrating and promoting best practices and learning&#x2019;s of community driven climate adaptation mechanisms especially in hard to reach and vulnerable areas will have the potential to influence the policy, strategies and practices of the government.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This British Council- CSSP extension project aims to strengthen resilience capacity of the target group through strategic investments focusing on demonstrating/promoting green energy technologies (finalizing construction of Pico hydro power) and practices maintaining eco system, supporting communities access to the product of Pico hydro power (access to rural electrification for off- grid communities), institutional building, evidence generation and promoting learning&#x2019;s.</narrative>
  </description>
